  "text": "We used cyclical stretch as a model of atrial overload caused by disease states that create a substrate for AF. It is not known whether the mechanisms described in our experimental model could be extrapolated to humans. We tested a limited number of mechanisms and signalling pathways that are often activated in ventricular disease as well as mechanisms that have been described in atrial fibrillation. It is likely that other signalling pathways are also activated, but this warrants further investigation. In vitro, stretch of atrial and ventricular cardiomyocytes can be dissected. In vivo, however, atrial fibrillation results in a high ventricular rate which has been shown to be an important causal factor of atrial remodelling [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
